headline: Nike earnings, Fed comments, pending home sales: What to Watch
summary: Asking for a Trend host Josh Lipton goes over the top stories to watch on Thursday, June 26. McCormick (MKC) will be reporting earnings before the opening bell and Nike (NKE) will be releasing its fourth quarter report after the closing bell, with analysts expecting a sales drop from Nike. Cleveland Fed president Beth Hammack will deliver remarks. Pending home sales data for May will be released, with economists expecting the same number from the month prior. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Asking for a Trend here.
